Reference-contexts: In section 3.3 we revisit the Forest example introduced in Chapter 2, and pose spatial queries using the OGIS extension of SQL. 3.1 Relational Algebra Relational algebra is a formal query language associated with the relational model <ref> [Ramakrishnan, 1998] </ref>. There are five basic operators in this algebra selection, projection, union, cross-product, difference. The fundamental property of all of these operators is that they accept relations as arguments and return a relation as the result.
